\par Date of birth:\tab \tab \tab 1883
\par Gender: \tab \tab \tab Male\tab \tab 
\par Marital status: \tab \tab \tab Married\tab 
\par Occupation: \tab \tab \tab Architect
\par Geographic region: \tab \tab Wales
\par 
\par 
\par I:\tab And when were you married?
\par 
\par CW:\tab 1915, beginning of 1915.
\par 
\par I:\tab When were you born?
\par 
\par CW:\tab 1883, May 28th.
\par 
\par I:\tab Where?
\par 
\par CW:\tab At Gayton, in Northamptonshire.
\par 
\par I:\tab How many years did you live in the house you were born in?
\par 
\par CW:\tab About four.
\par 
\par I:\tab And that was in Gayton?
\par 
\par CW:\tab Gayton, Northamptonshire; a college living to which my father went because he went ... he \tab was tutor of his college, and so on and in those days, if you married you were thrown out \tab 
and you were given a college living, you see. You had to take holy orders in order to be a \tab don, do you see. He wasn't a natural parson at all but he had to. And so we were at Gayton, \tab 
and then they had six children, at Gayton, six little boys and when they'd finished breeding t\tab hey retired to Glasfryd, which is the Ellis home, in Caernarvonshire. That was where I was \tab brought up.
\par 
\par I:\tab You said you had 6 brothers?
\par 
\par CW:\tab Six brothers, alas. I mean my poor mother would have very much liked a daughter.
\par 
\par I:\tab What sort of spacing was there between them, do you remember?
\par 
\par CW:\tab Oh, I think pell-mell, because she wasn't at Gayton very long and' we were all born there. \tab And I'm the last survivor. I was No.4.
\par 
\par I:\tab How old was your father when you were born?
\par 
\par CW:\tab Well, '83. He was born in '33, so he was 50.
\par 
\par I:\tab Where did he come from originally?
\par 
\par CW:\tab Well, Glasfryd, and here. This was the Williams house and that was the Ellis house which \tab was the main place. Where my elder brother succeeded there, and the next brother, who \tab 
should have had this, he was killed in the Boer War, so I succeeded to this.
\par 
\par I:\tab What was your father's occupation?
\par 
\par CW:\tab An academic. He was ... he got every possible prize and scholarship, both at school and at \tab Cambridge and was third wrangler of his year. In some things he was senior wrangler, but \tab 
he just missed it somehow. He was third wrangler, and then tutor and mathematics coach \tab and when he retired to Glasfryd he spent his time partially doing astronomical mathematics \tab 
as a diversion, and chess problems, and reading Greek and Latin, and so forth. And looking \tab after the estate, and shooting, and like ... a quiet, retired life, which is what he liked, after \tab working very, very hard at Cambridge 'till' he married.

\par 
\par I:\tab Presumably he didn't have any sort of casual or part time jobs?
\par 
\par CW:\tab No. Another thing, he was a very keen sailor, amateur sailor. I remember he had a launch \tab when he retired and then ... though generally he was very economical, he suddenly had a \tab 
tremendous splurge and bought a great big 70 ton yacht from Southampton with a crew of 5 \tab \{laughter\} and had to up and have himself built shore quarters for the considerable crew, \tab but then was so poor at the 
cost of it all he gave it up again. And also, she was so big, her \tab draught was so great; she couldn't get into 'any of the local harbours, so that didn't do any... \tab But he was always keen about sailing; he always had a boat of some sort.
\par 
\par I:\tab Presumably he was never out of work? He was never unemployed?
\par 
\par CW:\tab How do you mean?
\par 
\par I:\tab He was never without a job?
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \fi-720\li720\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0\pararsid8738534 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 CW:\tab 
No, doing something. And then he was fairly regular on the Bench at Pwllheli. I remember staying with Lloyd George down at Churt and at dinner, think
ing that ... you know, he knew that my family had been very antagonistic to him because they were Tories and he was not and furthermore, he'd been stumping the country during the Boer War, you see, pro-Boer, lecturing in our own village chapel, and that s
o
rt of thing, just after my brother had been killed and so that didn't go down very well, and he went out of his way to say how much he'd always respected my father for his complete impartiality and wisdom and justice, and all the rest of it. My father was
 he was completely bilingual which I'm afraid ... which had been the family tradition which, alas, ended with him. I picked up what I did as a child and never pursued it.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid917675 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
\par I:\tab How old was your mother when you were born?
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \fi-720\li720\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0\pararsid8738534 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 CW:\tab I think she was born in about '51
, lived to be 92, and she had serious thoughts about being professionally an artist. She'd attended the Slade School of Painting and attended John Ruskin's lectures and was very good indeed. She had quite an architectural sense, wonderful sketches, travel
l
ing, of architecture and so on, but was particularly keen on horses and indeed illustrated a book that I had as a child called "Black Beauty" with her drawings. And indeed, I think it is a near thing as to whether my father's declaration was made when she
 was high up on a ladder painting a frieze \{laughter\}, and I think it was quite a near thing as to whether she married or did go on as an artist, in which case I shouldn't have been here, probably.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid917675 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
\par I:\tab You can't remember how old she was when you were born?
\par 
\par CW:\tab Well, she was born in '51, I think, and I was born in '83, so you can work it out.
\par 
\par I:\tab After she was married she continued painting, I presume?
\par 
\par CW:\tab Oh, yes, I've got ... In fact, that early part is covered by my first premature autobiography.
\par 
\par I:\tab Did she have anyone in to look after the children while she was working?
\par 
\par CW:\tab Oh, yes, we always had nurses and nursemaids.
\par 
\par I:\tab I'd like to ask you now about life at home when you were a child up to the time you left \tab school.
\par 
\par CW:\tab Well, I practically always \{unclear\} went back gleefully to Glasfyd for holidays, and in the \tab winter it was shooting and ponies.
\par 
\par I:\tab Can you remember about Glasfryd, how many rooms were there in the house?
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \fi-720\li720\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0\pararsid8738534 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 CW:\tab \{Tape slips\}
 "The Archdeacon, from all accounts, was a man of many parts 
with a passion for science, especially chemistry and metallurgy, some of his laboratory equipment surviving at Glasfryd to this day. In 1809 when the, Archdeacon's son had succeeded him, Edmund Hyde Hall describe Glasfryd heirs the seat of the Reverend Th
o
mas Ellis near a small lake of the same name, and this and several rushy islands were haunts of wild duck, and other than this place I scarcely know a spot within the county more susceptible of rural beauty and polish". The Archdeacon's picture, a full le
n
gth picture of him in the dining room, very elegant. "Since his day other Ellises seem to have had their go at the house and pretty wildly, and even after my father's drastic efforts at rationalisation the layout and internal planning showed small regard 
f
or any logical sequence and was, indeed, chaotic. Starting at the extreme south-western end and working northwards round two or three right-angled bends with turns this way and that, the several rooms and offices succeeded one another thus: gunroom, baili
f
f's bothy, laundry, boot room, coalhouse, back entry, scullery, lavatory, larders, back stairs, kitchen, pantry, servants' hall, side entry, main entrance hall, business room, drawing room, entrance hall, front porch, great hall, cloakroom, dining room, s
t
udy, conservatory, schoolroom, third staircase, bathroom with heating chamber under, lavatory, another entry, wine cellar, dairy, storeroom, yet another and final entry , old saddle room and ultimate ,lumber room. The two floors above were neither so exte
n
sive nor so incoherent yet, apart from the dairy and laundry maids and the coachman who, reluctantly, carried coal and cleaned boots, all had to be serviced by an indoor staff that never exceeded five. Yet no one of us at the time, staff, family nor anyon
e
 else, seemed ever to have blamed the haphazard planning for any inconvenience, unnecessary work or needless running around. In the 1950s/'60s amputated at both extremities and twice ingeniously further re-organised first by my elder brother and his wife 
a
nd then by his eldest son and his, the old house still retains its familiar character but none of its former intimidating drawbacks and is well adapted both for family life and entertaining. But even when I was a child my father's ambitious reconstruction
s had greatly improved the place's amenities" ... and so on. That's the sort of\bullet  house it was.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid917675 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
\par I:\tab That's really interesting. Did anyone else apart from your parents and brothers and sisters \tab live in the house?
\par 
\par CW:\tab I never had any sisters.
\par 
\par I:\tab Oh, sorry, yes.
\par 
\par I:\tab Did you have other relatives, or lodgers, or anything like that?
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \fi-720\li720\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0\pararsid8738534 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 CW:\tab 
Very few. My father, even when he added to the house and there were new spare bedrooms and so on, you see, central heating and electric light and so on, he hated having what he c
alled 'strangers' in the house, and also greatly deprecated what he called 'gadding about', so that one ached and ached as a boy to see anybody outside the family. And I remember looking forward to and looking back to as a great treat an old archbishop co
m
ing to see us and stay, and his old Cambridge dons, and being disappointed .... Dons: I'd got a sort of quixotic idea of dons. I thought the Cambridge sort inferior to the Spanish, and so old, most of them they seemed almost another species altogether. An
d
 with roads and transport of that day, you see, we were awfully isolated; especially as the range of our ponies as being the sort of limiting radius, and he didn't approve of gadding about, as I say, so we didn't go ... and with the roads and vehicles and
 horses of those days, you see, 12 miles was equivalent to 100 miles today.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid917675 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
\par I:\tab What about the servants? You've talked a little bit about the servants in the house. You said \tab you had five, yes?
\par 
\par CW:\tab Yes.
\par 
\par I:\tab What sort of things did they do?
\par 
\par CW:\tab Well, there was the cook and kitchen maid - scullery maid - and parlour maid, and two \tab housemaids, I suppose, they shared things to some extent.
\par 
\par I:\tab And a gardener, probably?
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \fi-720\li720\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0\pararsid8738534 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 CW:\tab 
Whereas in ... I altered the house where the lists of the servants and their duties was up, which ended at the bottom with 'two lamp boys', you see.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid917675 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
\par I:\tab To light the lamps?
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \fi-720\li720\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0\pararsid8738534 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 CW:\tab 
They did nothing else but fill and trim and light lamps. Forty of them. And I remember going up at Wentworth Wood House ... I turned Stowe, which is the biggest coun
try house in England into a public school, and just for fun before I started I counted on the survey plan all the rooms, large and small, and there were 400, and one tap which was down in the basement. And I remember going ... After Stowe had become a pub
l
ic school, the next country house in England was Wentworth Woodhouse and I was up there in wartime and Lady Fitzwilliam said 'I expect you'd like to look round the house ,come along'. And we walked and walked for a couple of hours, I suppose, round and sa
w
 part of it. And I said, 'Goodness, gracious, you must have needed quite a staff to run this in peacetime - this was wartime, they were only living in part of the house - and she said, 'Yes, indeed'. And I said, 'Well, what?' She said, 'well, we found we 
couldn't be really comfortable with fewer than 75 indoors'.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid917675 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
\par I:\tab Goodness me! \{Laughter\}
\par 
\par CW:\tab Mostly waiting on each other, you see. Steward's room, housekeeper's room, servants' hall.
\par 
\par I:\tab Did they have a servants hall at Glasfryd, then?
\par 
\par CW:\tab Oh, yes.
\par 
\par I:\tab Where did they sleep and eat?
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \fi-720\li720\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0\pararsid8738534 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 CW:\tab 
Oh, in their own rooms. They slept in very nice rooms, and my mother was very good with them and they stayed for years.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid917675 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \fi-720\li720\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0\pararsid8738534 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 I:\tab 
Did your mother supervise the housework personally, or did she pass orders through senior servants?
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid917675 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \fi-720\li720\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0\pararsid8738534 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 CW:\tab 
Oh, yes, she did, quite, easily and they were good and knew her ways and she knew theirs. And she took a motherly interest in them.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid917675 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
\par I:\tab Did you feel at ease with the servants?
\par 
\par CW:\tab Yes, perfectly.
\par 
\par I:\tab How did the servants and the members of the family address each other?
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \fi-720\li720\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0\pararsid8738534 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 CW:\tab 
I was Master Clough, and the others ... mostly ... the parlour maid was always just her surname, Drage, for most-of the time. Bostock, another one I remember, and the cook always Mrs. Somebody, even if she wasn't married. A courtesy title.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid917675 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
\par I:\tab Did you feel that any of the servants were interested in you as a person?
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \fi-720\li720\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0\pararsid8325038 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 CW:\tab 
Certainly the parlour maid always did because she'd originally come as my nurse, you see, and was with us, I suppose for 30 years.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid917675 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
\par I:\tab Did your mother give any sort of moral guidance to the servants?
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \fi-720\li720\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0\pararsid8325038 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 CW:\tab 
There were family prayers, which I dodged as often as I could, but they'd all come rustling in, you know, and kneel down and sing a hymn or whatever it was.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid917675 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
\par I:\tab Did the servants have any sort of spare time in which they could do what they liked?
\par 
\par CW:\tab Oh, yes. Yes, of course. They had ... I don't know ... their half-days off.
\par 
\par I:\tab And they could go out of the home, presumably?
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \fi-720\li720\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0\pararsid8325038 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 CW:\tab 
Oh, yes. But I remember I had an aunt who had a much larger household, there were 12 servants indoors, and she was outraged and gave them a terrific wigging because some of them dared to wear flowery hats on Sunday, instead of black.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid917675 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
\par I:\tab But your mother, presumably, wasn't so strict?
\par 
\par CW:\tab Oh, no.
\par 
\par I:\tab And they could come in and out when they liked, presumably, when it was ... ?
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \fi-720\li720\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0\pararsid8325038 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 CW:\tab 
Yes. It was all very easy-going. They were kept up to doing their jobs properly, whatever they were, dusting, or cleaning, or cooking or whatever it was.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid917675 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
\par I:\tab How did the housework go? Presumably that was all done by the servants?
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \fi-720\li720\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0\pararsid8325038 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 CW:\tab 
Oh, I couldn't tell you, I mean, it was done. They started pretty early, I think, you know, about half past seven in the morning. There was a lot done before our breakfast which was half past 8.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid917675 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
\par I:\tab Was any washing sent out?
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \fi-720\li720\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0\pararsid8325038 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 CW:\tab No, 
we had the ... Apart from the regular ... the house staff, there were laundry maids, and dairy maids, Katherine \{missing\}
 who ran the ... You see, there was a home farm and the dairy and she made butter and produced cream and soon, from the milk. And all the laundry was done at home, in the washing room and the drying room.
\par 
\par I:\tab Who was responsible, for repairs and improvements to the house?
\par 
\par CW:\tab Well, my father had this great re-building which lasted two years, during which we occupied a house we had ... a 
seaside house at Abersoch, which was very pleasant in a way because of sailing and sea fishing and so on. But I was devastated because all this building was going on and I wasn't there. That was what I was really interested in, passionately interested in 
from when I was about six, rebuilding. And so he looked after the fabric of, the house, so to speak; my mother its adornment, decoration and that sort of thing.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid917675 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
\par I:\tab You told me there was a nanny responsible for the children?
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \fi-720\li720\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0\pararsid8325038 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 CW:\tab Oh, yes, until taken over b
y a governess: There was a succession of governesses after nurses, you seep and nursemaids.
\par 
\par I:\tab What exactly were her duties?
\par 
\par CW:\tab Whose duties?
\par 
\par I:\tab The nanny's.
\par 
\par CW:\tab Oh, sort of valeting the child, seeing to its meals and being nice to it and talking to i
t, I suppose. I can't remember much about the ... I remember when I was I suppose about 5 or 6 my nurse, who was being courted by a sea captain, a rather tipsy little man whom my mother, incautiously in my hearing, \{I remember\}
 saying, 'oh, he's little better than a barrel on legs'. I thought this a splendid description and I asked my nurse if she didn't think so, too. This was her beau, you see. She did not! Nor did he and it all ended in lamentations and tears \{laughter\}.

\par 
\par I:\tab Were you allowed to see your parents anywhere in the house or were there specific rooms to which the children were confined?
\par 
\par CW:\tab No, we saw them at ... insofar as our meals were in the dining room. Of course, we met them at meals, and my mother was very much more accessible than my f
ather who rather shut himself up in his study, reading or writing, or doing his chess problems or mathematics, or whatever it was.
\par 
\par I:\tab Did your father take an interest in sort of taking care of your sort of everyday needs at all? Dressing you or undressing you, or anything like that, or was it completely left up to the servants and your mother?
\par 
\par CW:\tab Oh, he did nothing of that sort at all, no.
\par 
\par I:\tab And presumably he didn't take you out for walks and things like that?
\par 
\par CW:\tab Oh, sometimes. And then, when I was a little older, shooting, which I didn't care about, much.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid917675 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
\par I:\tab Were there any tasks that you had to do as a child around the house?
\par 
\par CW:\tab No, practically nothing.
\par 
\par I:\tab And presumably none of your brothers did, either?
\par 
\par CW:\tab No. I remember at one period I got a penny an hour for weeding.
\par 
\par I:\tab Did the older children help the younger children with things they found if difficult?
\par 
\par CW:\tab No, not much. We were really all rather independent going our several ways.
\par 
\par I:\tab Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time in your schooldays?
\par 
\par CW:\tab Oh, yes, certainly.
\par 
\par I:\tab What time was that?
\par 
\par CW:\tab I suppose it got gradually later, that's all I can remember.
\par 
\par I:\tab Did your mother or anyone else put you to bed?
\par 
\par CW:\tab I don't remember that. I must have been quite ... from about 5 I'm sure I put myself to bed.
\par 
\par I:\tab Did you share a bedroom or bed with anyone?
\par 
\par CW:\tab No, as far as I can remember I always had my own room.
\par 
\par I:\tab And all your brothers had their own rooms, as well?
\par 
\par CW:\tab They had their own rooms, too.
\par 
\par I:\tab Did you have a bathroom?
\par 
\par CW:\tab Yes.
\par 
\par I:\tab How often did you bath?
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \fi-720\li720\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0\pararsid8325038 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 CW:\tab 
I don't think we bathed more than regularly once a week. And so it was at school, too. Once a week.
\par 
\par I:\tab And did you get clean clothes once a week, or more often than that?
\par 
\par CW:\tab I think once a week. Almost certainly.
\par 
\par I:\tab Where did the family have their meals?
\par 
\par CW:\tab In the dining room.
\par 
\par I:\tab Were there any occasions when they ate in another room?
\par 
\par CW:\tab Tea in the drawing room, sometimes, or the hall, according to whether there was a party or not.
\par 
\par I:\tab Do you remember what sort of cooking arrangements?
\par 
\par CW:\tab Oh, a large range, big old range, I think, that got very hot, like old-fashioned ranges do.
\par 
\par I:\tab When was breakfast eaten, at what time?
\par 
\par CW:\tab I think 8 or half past. And there was a rule, a family rule, that we children had to appear at breakfast in our outdoor boots.
\par 
\par I:\tab Were all the members of the family there at breakfast, normally?
\par 
\par I:\tab What did you usually eat or drink for breakfast?
\par 
\par CW:\tab Oh, always porridge, eaten with salt and milk, and then eggs or bacon or fish, or something of that sort.
\par 
\par I:\tab When was the midday meal?
\par 
\par CW:\tab At 1 o'clock.
\par 
\par I:\tab What sort of things did you have for that?
\par 
\par CW:\tab Generally, I suppose, a joint of some sort, or cold ham, or brawn, or something of that sort, or again, fish or game in due season.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid917675 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
\par I:\tab And then the evening meal?
\par 
\par CW:\tab Well, the same sort of thing only more elaborate.
\par 
\par I:\tab And what time was that?
\par 
\par CW:\tab I think in the evening it was half past 7.
\par 
\par I:\tab Did you bake your own bread, make your own jam or anything like that?
\par 
\par CW:\tab Yes, all that.
\par 
\par I:\tab Bottle fruit and vegetables, make pickles, wine and medicines?
\par 
\par CW:\tab And the kitchen garden grew all the vegetables and fruit and things.
\par 
\par I:\tab Did you brew any beer in the family?
\par 
\par CW:\tab No.
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \fi-720\li720\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0\pararsid8325038 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 I:\tab 
Did the kitchen garden supply everything, or did you have to buy any fruit or vegetables at all?
\par 
\par CW:\tab Well, if any, very rarely.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 What sort of livestock did you keep, do you remember?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
Oh, well, cows for milking, and pigs, sheep, usual stock, mixed farming.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
My father had a bailiff who looked after all that, you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 I}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038\charrsid8738534 :}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Did you eat meat every day?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Yes, I suppose so.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 I}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038\charrsid8738534 :}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Did you ever get extra meat, such as rabbit, from poaching?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 :\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
Oh, very well, yes, I mean that was part of the meat; game and hares and rabbits and, of course, poultry, too.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Did your father poach, in fact, or did he do it quite legally?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
Oh, well, you see, it's quite a big estate, and plenty of shooting on it of all sorts, and he was rather a good shot.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Do you ever remember your mother going without food or less food so that the family could have more?
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid917675 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Were you allowed to talk during meals?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Yes, of course.
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \fi-720\li720\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0\pararsid8325038 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Did you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked, or did you have to eat everything?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
No, given a ... we were allowed a certain latitude. If we were too tiresome they, would say 'well, jolly well go without' if we didn't want it. We weren't forced to eat anything.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
If there was something on the table you wanted like the salt could you ask someone to pass it to you or did you have to wait until somebody offered it to you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
Oh, no, certainly ask, or snatch \{laughter\}.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Presumably you could ask for a second helping?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Any time we wanted it, yes.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way and sit in a certain way?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
I suppose so. Well, I mean, one found oneself holding them in the accepted fashion so I suppose at some time one learnt to do it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Could you bring toys and books to the table?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Well, we never did.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 When did you leave the table, when you liked or did you have to wait until everybody else had finished?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
I think until everyone had finished.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Did you always have the same places?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 At table?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 How was the meal served, presumably by servants?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Yes, sometimes ..
. I mean, the meal was brought in by servants and I think they sort of started off and then I think we generally ... well, certainly at breakfast and lunch we looked after ourselves. And at dinner I think the parlour maid, you know, cleared the places and
 brought the next course and handed it round.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid917675 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \fi-720\li720\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0\pararsid1471075 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Do you remember in what order the meals were served out in? Did your father get served first, or the children first, or what?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
Well, you see, sometimes he was carving, sometimes my mother was carving and sometimes the thing didn't need carving, it was already served like that. I don't think there was any regular routine about it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Where did your younger brother sit before they could feed themselves?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f0\fs24\insrsid8325038   }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Did they sort of eat in the nursery?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Oh, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Where did the servants eat?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 In the servants' hall.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Did they have different food?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
Partly different, partly the same. It all depended. I mean, if there were special delicacies they probably didn't get 'em \{laughter\}.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
Yes. Especially for me because she was interested in visual things very much, and artistic, and so on, and I hadn't much, really, in common with my father who was purely academic, really. Though not ... when I say 'purely', he w
as also interested in sailing and shooting, and so on.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Did your mother show affection?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Oh, indeed, yes. Very much so.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8325038 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Could you share sort of personal worries and things like that with your parents?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid1471075\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid1471075 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
I suppose one did. I can't recall any particular things.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid1471075  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 I can't recall having any particular ...
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid1471075 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Problems?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid1471075\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid1471075 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
Or complex worries. One was sometimes less happy than at other times, that's all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid1471075 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid1471075\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid1471075 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 I don't know. They didn't seem 
surprised at the way, in fact, we did behave, which was in no particular way, really. I think we were quite a civilised community, not really tightly bound together but going our own ways, as it were, and respecting each other's liberties. We were allowed
 to very much go off on our own. My mother was the very queen of non-fussers. She was fine and she thought that adventures, in reason, were only natural.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid1471075 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 How were you expected to behave towards your brothers? Could you hit them hit back if you were hit,
 and things like that?
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid917675 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \fi-720\li720\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0\pararsid1471075 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid1471075\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f0\fs24\insrsid1471075 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
I can't remember any fisticuffs at all. In a way I was, for a spell anyhow, somewhat lonely because I was not grand enough for my two elder brothers and too grand for my two younger brothers. I was a sort of sandwich boy.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid1471075 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Can you remember what sort of person your parents hoped you'd grow up to be?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid1471075\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid1471075 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
I've no idea what ... I mean, they hoped I'd have a useful, happy life and that's about all; not disgrace the family.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid15562405 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Did your parents consider certain things important in life? Did they have a certain outlook on life?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid15562405\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid15562405 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
Yes, I think they were both very high minded. I mean, they would have been desperately unhappy and shocked if any of us had sort of gone off the rails in any way, which fortunately we didn't. My father wa
s always rather disappointed that we weren't more intellectual. He had, as I say, every kind of academic honour and so-forth and hoped- that we might be the same, but we weren't a prize-winning lot at all. I think we ... the main thing was I think we were
 rather late-flowering varieties, so to speak.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid15562405 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 What did your parents think of swearing?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid15562405\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid15562405 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
I don't think they look any line about it. I remember learning the word 'bloody' from one of the workmen who were working on Glasfryd, you see, and I tried it on my governess to her considerable shock, but nothing happened otherwise.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid15562405 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 When grownups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid15562405\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid15562405 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Oh, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid15562405 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 If you did something your parents disapproved of what would happen?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid15562405\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid15562405 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
Well, depends what. I remember,
 I think where my father was rather harsh once, they were just going abroad and I borrowed his bicycle I'd just learnt to bicycle without leave, and smashed one of the pedals. I was skidding - a lovely feeling - skidding on the mud, like that and suddenly
 
off went one of the pedals. And he was just going off and instead of leaving me to use it while he was away he said he thought it would be better to be put away and locked up, so I had nothing. That was very sad. But otherwise there was no question of pun
ishments of anything of that- sort. I can't remember any punishments, or being kept in, or anything.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid15562405 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 And you weren't beaten or things like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid15562405\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid15562405 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 No, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid15562405 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Would you say that you received the ideas you had about how to behave from your parents?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid15562405\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid15562405 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Yes, I suppose so.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid15562405 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 And did one or other of them play a more important part?
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \fi-720\li720\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0\pararsid15562405 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid15562405\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f0\fs24\insrsid15562405 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
Oh, yes, my mother, certainly, because I saw much more of her, you see. We were much more akin; and of course, she wasn't ... My father was much older, too, you see, much older than my mother, and more withdrawn.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
Oh, yes, well slightly. It was exciting. Of course, one had a few presents and some ... and a birthday cake. One was made much of.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Did you have a tea party with guests?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
Well, we were so far away and so few neighbours at all that parties were very rare, indeed.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Can you remember anything you did with your mother and father together on Christmas Day?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 We always went to church 
in the morning, and we generally had somebody staying. Very often a very charming and amusing maiden aunt who was rather fun; and presents all laid out on a long Elizabethan table in the great hall, which we weren't allowed to look at until after breakfas
t. Having started, of course, with a stocking, which was very exciting.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Did you have any musical instruments in your home?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Only a piano.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Who played?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
My mother, and we were very unmusical, really.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Nobody sang, then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Did you ever have any sort of musical evening round the piano with your mother?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
No, not really. We were awfully unmusical, really.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Did your parents play any games with you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
Played a little very primitive cricket and tennis, and I think that was all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Were there lots of books in the house?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
Yes, lots of books, a great many of them very old books, you know, 17th, 18th, even 16th century. I don't know how they'd accumulated, and then we were given books, amongst our Christmas .presents there 
were always books. There was some old boy who for years always sent me that year's Henty. Did you ever read Henty, G.A. Henty? I suppose he wrote more boys' books than anybody else. Quite good of that sort, semi-historical you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Did you have newspapers and magazines coming into the house regularly?
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \fi-720\li720\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0\pararsid10578772 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f0\fs24\insrsid10578772 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
Daily newspaper. In fact, two. The Standard and The Daily Graphic, both long dailies. I remember when my father was abroad and the papers hadn't stopped coming and on April 1st the Standard duly arriv
ed through the post and I hid it away until the following year, April 1st, and popped it in instead of the current one. He wrote an angry letter to the editor saying that it may amuse your staff sending me a paper a year old. And then I confessed and then
 he was jolly angry with me. I remember seeing the first photograph that was in The Daily Graphic, otherwise they were a all sketches, you see, pen and ink, reproduced ... a very blurred photograph of a steamer on the rocks.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Presumably your mother and father read a lot?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
My father read quite a lot, largely the classics, and my mother was fairly well ... I mean, she read Jane Austen, and the poets quite a lot. You see, she was born in the house that Shelley had at \{blank\}. I designed the monument to g
o in the garden there in memory of Shelley, and she'd known Emerson, too, my mother had. And Ruskin. And my father was awarded a ... given a commemorative gold watch by his college and the Royal Humane Society's gold medal for a very gallant life-saving a
nd Ruskin designed the wreath to go round this, and I had it with Ruskin's letter, and they were both destroyed in the fire. You see, this place was entirely gutted by fire in '51. Everything went, all books and papers and records.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Do you remember a funeral in the family?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
My father's funeral ... Well, I suppose everybody else had a funeral, but his funeral ... he was buried in a pre-arranged enclosure by the orchard, kitchen garden, with yew hedge round and wrought iron gates and so on and carried d
own the avenue and buried there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Did lots of people come to the funeral?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
Well, only ... No, it was a private funeral, just tenants and the household, I think.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Did they wear special clothes, mourning clothes?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 You told me a bit abou
t the fact that you didn't have many friends and neighbours. You didn't go visiting much and presumably your father didn't like having people to stay in the house.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
No, and partly our country house neighbours, we had Broom Hall on one side and \{missing\}
 on the other, both very large estates, each with its own pack of hounds, each with its own yacht, stables full of horses, large domestic staffs and that sort of thing and all our neighbours in country houses were rather philistine, like that, and hadn't 
much really in common with my very studious academic father and artistic mother. And I don't think they found exchange of visits very rewarding and I don't think it was the miles of bad roads, so much as the fact that when they did meet they didn't find i
t very rewarding.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid10578772 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Were you ever taken out shopping?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid13714410\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid13714410 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
Yes. Sometimes Pwllheli, when my father went down to the Bench there I'd sometimes go with him, but very little. There was a village shop, a minimal village shop in \{missing\} and one in Llangybi a
nd another at Chwilog, which was about the range of our pony rides.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid917675 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid13714410 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Do you remember any outings, sort of Bank Holiday outings, or summer outings?
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \fi-720\li720\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0\pararsid13714410 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid13714410\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f0\fs24\insrsid13714410 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 No. We went, sometimes, expeditions. Like going over to Brynkir from ... Brynkir Hall which is a deso
late place, that was about the limit in distance, or \{missing\} or \{missing\}, but, you know, either taking a picnic or meeting somebody there.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid917675 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid13714410 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Did you ever go away on holiday?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid13714410\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid13714410 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
Not as a small child, never. Hardly at all until I went abroad on my own, really.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid13714410 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Can you remember how you spent Saturdays in those days?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid13714410\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid13714410 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
Well, in the winter if there was a meet anywhere within reach hunting on ponies.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid13714410 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 And Sundays?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid13714410\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid13714410 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
Sunday was always clouded by fine raiment and religious observances.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid13714410 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Did you have Sunday clothes?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid13714410\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid13714410 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
We more or less had to go to church.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid13714410 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 In special clothes, I mean, you sort of dressed up?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid13714410\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid13714410 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
Yes, dress up for Sunday. I remember some people still turning up in top hats.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid13714410 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Were you allowed to play games or work on Sundays?
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \fi-720\li720\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0\pararsid13714410 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid13714410\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f0\fs24\insrsid13714410 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
No. Well, we were discouraged from that because it was disapproved of by our neighbours, you see, non-conformist neighbours who didn't like ball games much at any time, especially on Sunday.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid13714410 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Presumably your parents went to church, too?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Y
es. And my father, you know, who had really retired, on Easter or on special times would very often preach, and preach very well indeed, too, when he preached in English. When he preached in Welsh, of course, I didn't understand it and the service was adj
usted according to the congregation.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 This was Church of England, wasn't it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Did they go every Sunday?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
Not every, but most. Sometimes we walked, sometimes we drove.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \fi-720\li720\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0\pararsid5179722 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Did you go to Sunday School?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
I don't think there was any within reach.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 So presumably you didn't have Sunday School outings, or anything like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
No. We always gave a school treat at Glasfryn to two or three schools, certainly Llangybi, Llannor and Llanaelhaearn. They all came marching up together and they had sports and tea and all the, rest of it, you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Did you take part in any other social activities organised by the church?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Did you belong to the choir?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
No. Not until I went to school, not because I could sing of had an ear or anything, because ... I don't know how I contrived it. I wangled it somehow because the choir had outings and I wanted to go on one of these outings.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Do you remember if the church had a temperance club?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 No \{laughter\}
. I don't think they existed.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Was Grace said at meals?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
I think it was. I think just 'Benedictus bene \{missing\}', a Latin thing, when my father was there. Otherwise I don't think we did.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
I think we must have been but it didn't last long.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 And did you ever have family prayers?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
Oh, every day, alas, before breakfast.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
Not much. He was basically Conservative and so, I think, was my mother. Politics loomed very small at the time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Do you know why he was Conservative?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
I think his father had been and his grandfather had been \{laughter\}, for no better reason.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Do you remember your father and your mother voting in a general election? Before 19l9?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 I suppose so.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid917675 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 You don't remember it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 No, I don't remember it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 You just presume that they'd vote Conservative if they did?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Yes. I don't remember.
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \fi-720\li720\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0\pararsid5179722 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 In some places at that time men felt they risked losing their jobs or their house if they voted differently f
rom their employer. Do you know if your father felt himself under any of that kind of pressure to vote for a particular party?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
Well, he wouldn't because he was a local landowner. He never brought pressure on anybody, not like old \{missing\} did, at \{missing\}. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Your father presumably didn't work the Conservative Party or anything during an election?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Or your mother?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
No. My uncle, Sir Osmond Williams of \{missing\} Castle, of course, he was Member for Merioneth, a Liberal. 'A red hot Radical ', they called him \{laughter\}
. He ... his father had been there before him, he'd been the first Liberal Member for Merioneth. It had always been Tory before.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Did your parents take part in any other political activity, other than at election time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
When your parents were not doing their work how did they spend their time? You've talked to me about that, actually, about your father sailing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
Well, they occasionally went abroad, and they'd very adventurously on their honeymoon gone right up the Nile which was... when? I don't know what date that was, but quite early. You know, in one of these sailing \{missing\}
 and so on. And at home my mother did a bit of gardening and my father went around the farm, the home farm, and that sort of thing, and did a certain amount of tree-planting, looking after that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Did your mother ever go out and enjoy herself on her own?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
Well, that was very much discouraged by my father who ... you see, we had a pair of carriage horses but they were a
lso supposed to work on the farm and earn their keep, you see, and he generally said that they couldn't go out because they were wanted for something-or-other, you see. And my mother belonged to a large family, the Graveleys, and sisters around, Lady Will
iams at \{missing\} and Hilda Graves at Tenralth, and Lady Smythe who was a darling, and Aunt Edie Hansard, and so on, and she liked to see them when she could, and did when she could, but it was rather limited by my father's rationing of horsepower \{
laughter\}.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Did your father spend most evenings in a week at home, then?
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid917675 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Did your father ever attend clubs or pubs?
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s15\ql \fi-720\li720\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0\pararsid5179722 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Well, he belonged to the Athenaeum most of his life, in London. That's the only club he ever belonged to.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 And did your mother go along there? Or is it men only?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
Men only. Very much so. They've got a women's side now, I believe. I belong. I found myself the Father of the Club and it's by no means a young man's club.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Did your father take part in any sport?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 No. Wel
l, yes. As a young man he'd been a keen mountaineer, in fact, one of the founders of the Alpine Club and when the Alpine Club had its Jubilee, or whatever it was some years ago I sent them his staff which had got a pewter sort of band going round with the
 summits that he'd been up engraved on it. He was a Bard; his Bardic title was \{missing\}.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Did he ever attend the races, or bet?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
Never. Nor have I. The only time a friend of mine insisted on taking me to the Derby, hired a bus you know, the open top
ped bus. And during the actual Derby I was asleep on the floor down below and never saw it. He said, 'you must come and see the Derby' and I said, 'well, all right' and I went, but I wasn't much amused.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Did your father or mother belong to any savings clubs?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
No sisters, again. Oh, perfectly all right in rather a detached way. We all went our several ways, I had my concerns and they had theirs.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Was there one of them that was particularly close to you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 As a child who did you play with?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
I didn't play much, I was busy constructing things.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 On your own, mainly?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid5179722 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 
On my own, and if I could do it secretly, all the better. Either building houses, or boats or water wheels, or whatever.
