\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid1928298\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid1928298 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Well, we saw
 our friends. We dined out and gave dinner parties. Went to the theatre. My wife for a long time was a theatre critic. We saw a lot of friends, in their houses or in our own.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid1928298 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Did you take any interest in sport or anything like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid1928298\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid1928298 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Less than none
. I was dragged, I remember, by ... who was it? Oh, Evelyn Waugh's brother, you know, Alec Waugh. He said, 'you must attend a soccer match. You don't know what your country's like without it'. He bought and gave me a cloth cap; he let me off a rattle and 
booked a front seat at a cup final, or something, and dragged me along. And I went. And in the same way I was dragged to the Derby and went to sleep during the actual race.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid1928298 I:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Did you ever go to pubs or anything like that? Clubs or pubs?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid1928298\charrsid8738534 CW:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid1928298 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid8738534\charrsid8738534 Never to pubs
, or hardly ever. I belonged to various social clubs, Guards Club, The Atheneum and Garrick, and so on, to a couple of night clubs but I didn't often go.
\par 
